    <!-- The new article tag. The id is supplied so it can be scrolled into view. -->
    <h2>
        <a href="/jedi">Jedi</a>
        <a class="go_up" href="#"><img src="images/up.png" width="40" title="Go Up" alt="Up"></a>
    </h2>

    <div class="line"></div>

    <div class="articleBody clear">
        <figure class="figure_home">
            <!-- The figure tag marks data (usually an image) that is part of the article -->
            <a href="/jedi"><img src="images/jedi.jpg" width="900" title="Obi Wan Kenobi"
                    alt="Jedi" /></a>
        </figure>
        <blockquote>
            “For My Ally Is The Force, And A Powerful Ally It Is.”
        </blockquote>
        <p>-- Yoda</p>
        <p>
            A <strong>Jedi</strong> was a devotee to the ways of the Jedi
            Order, an ancient order of protectors united by their ability to
            harness the power of the Force. Adhering to a doctrine that
            favored the light side of the Force, the Jedi aspired to attain a
            state of inner tranquility through calmness and meditation while
            avoiding emotions affiliated with the dark side of the Force, such
            as anger and hatred. Nevertheless, Jedi philosophy did not forbid
            a Jedi from acting in self-defense or in the defense of others. To
            that end, the weapon of a Jedi was the lightsaber, a blade
            composed of pure energy and different colors such as blue, green,
            purple, or yellow.
        </p>
    </div>
</article>

